President Roh Moo-Hyun called for a probe into illegal wiretapping of conversations between South Korea's ambassador to the US and a Samsung executive.
Widespread corruption scandals in 2002 involved illicit donations by businesses to politicians.
Samsung was accused of donating funds to political parties, leading to arrests.
The businessman leaked the conversation to the press after failing to blackmail Samsung.
The NIS apologized for wiretapping, and prosecutors are investigating.
President Roh accepted the ambassador's resignation over the scandal.
Samsung apologized, and the NIS will conduct a thorough investigation into the slush funds scandal.
